text: Ahmad Galal () is an Egyptian footballer. He currently plays as a striker for Egypt's Arab Contractors SC. ==Career== Galal came to prominence on 27 January 2007 in the Egyptian Soccer Cup when, despite only playing in the second half of the game, he scored a hat-trick against Talkha Electricity Club. Al Ahly wound up winning the game 3-0. In the summer of 2007, Galal joined the Egyptian side El-Masry and scored a goal in his debut against Al Ahly in the Egyptian Premier League. ==External links== * Download Galal's Hat-trick against Talka Electricity, Egyptian Cup Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Egyptian footballers Category:Al Ahly SC players Category:Al Masry SC players Category:Association football forwards Category:People from Sharqia Governorate Category:Ittihad El Shorta SC players Category:Egyptian Premier League players
